---

[Maine regulators approve conservation plan, allowing completion of controversial NECEC line](https://www.pressherald.com/2025/11/20/maine-regulators-approve-conservation-plan-allowing-completion-of-controversial-necec-line/)

In response to environmental concerns, regulators at the Maine Department of Environmental Protection required NECEC to conserve 50,000 acres near the line. Regulators [approved the company’s proposal](https://www.pressherald.com/2025/11/20/maine-regulators-approve-conservation-plan-allowing-completion-of-controversial-necec-line/) in November, clearing the project’s final hurdle.

Avangrid [says the line](https://www.necleanenergyconnect.org/facts) will reduce energy costs in Maine by between $14 and $44 million. In Massachusetts, where most of the power will end up, the [projected savings](https://www.iberdrola.com/about-us/what-we-do/smart-grids/necec-project-canada-united-states-and-new-england) are about $150 million, according to Avangrid’s parent company, Iberdrola.

A spokesperson for Avangrid declined to comment on the project Monday.

